<h2> > What's it about? < </h2><br>

<img src="https://qph.fs.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-843133dbde6236cec846a814dcc80dbe" alt="Warhammer 40k New Logo">

<p>One of my favorite hobbies is table top wargaming. Out of all the table top wargames I have played, Games Workshop's <a  class="links" href="https://www.games-workshop.com/en-US/Warhammer-40-000/" target="_blank">Warhammer 40k</a> is my absolute favorite.
    The game, lore, and hobby aspect of it is what keeps me engaged in it. </p>
  
<br>
<div><h3>Why do I find this hobby interesting?</h3></div>
<p>Playing the game:</p>
<ul>
    <li>The game itself is complex and unique that nothing in the market (that I know of) plays like it.</li>
    <li>There is a very large variety of armies that all completely play differently from each other.</li>
    <li>Each faction in the game have sub-factions that also change the way how the army plays on the tabletop.</li>
  </ul>

<img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7c/Keno_mini_wargame.jpg" alt="Warhammer 40k Tabletop example" width="500" height="300">

<p>Hobby aspect:</p>
  <ul>
      <li>I love working with my hands. Cutting out parts from a sprue and gluing them together </li>
      <li>The Games Workshop models themselves are full of detail and are surprisingly high quality compared to other companies.</li>
      <li>Painting models can be very relaxing and allows me to use express my creativity on each model.</li>
    </ul>

<img src="https://www.scalemodelguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/Using_Xuron_cutter.jpg" alt="Cutters" width="500" height="300">

